cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with adversarial attacks and robust learning in classification algorithms, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses image datasets and discusses the effectiveness of the proposed methods in image classification, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a general framework for retraining algorithms, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
